errors.error_type: Elements must meet minimum color contrast ratio thresholds
errors.description: All text elements must have sufficient contrast between text in the foreground and background colors behind it in accordance with WCAG 2 AA contrast ratio thresholds.
errors.fix: Ensure that text has a contrast ratio of at least 4.5:1.

errors.error_type: ARIA input fields must have an accessible name
errors.description: Ensures every ARIA input field has an accessible name.
errors.fix: Add an accessible name to the input field using the aria-label or aria-labelledby attribute.

errors.description: Buttons must have discernible text that clearly describes the destination, purpose, function, or action for screen reader users.The input-button-name rule separates functionality from the button-name rule to ensure that input buttons have discernible text; advise relevant to input button names was incorrect for button elements.
errors.fix: Add discernible text to the button element.
